    "what_description": "Aquilaria parvifolia is a species of plant in the family Thymelaeaceae, native to tropical Asia. It is a small tree or shrub, growing up to 10 meters in height, with a broad, rounded crown and a short, straight trunk. The leaves are alternate, simple, and elliptical, measuring 2-5 centimeters in length, with a leathery texture and a crenate margin. The flowers are small, white, and arranged in axillary panicles, while the fruit is a red or purple drupe, 2-3 centimeters in length. The heartwood of this plant is highly prized for its resinous properties, which are used in traditional medicine and as a fixative in perfumery.",
