    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Aquilaria parvifolia are its ability to prevent the growth of harmful microorganisms. This is attributed to the antimicrobial properties, which are due to the presence of bioactive compounds such as flavonoids, terpenoids, and phenolic acids that exhibit antibacterial and antifungal activities. The plant's antioxidant properties help protect the body from oxidative stress by scavenging free radicals, thereby preventing cell damage and promoting overall well-being. Aquilaria parvifolia also possesses anti-inflammatory properties, which are mediated by saponins and volatile oils that reduce inflammation and alleviate symptoms associated with various diseases. Additionally, the antifungal properties of the plant help combat fungal infections, while its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties work synergistically to combat oxidative stress and inflammation.",
