    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Aquilaria parvifolia are aquilarin, oleanolic acid, ursolic acid, quercetin, and gallic acid, which have been identified as key bioactive compounds contributing to its medicinal properties. Aquilarin has been shown to possess antimicrobial and antifungal activities, while oleanolic acid and ursolic acid have been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory and hepatoprotective effects. Quercetin, a powerful flavonoid, has been demonstrated to have antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and anticancer properties. Gallic acid, a polyphenolic compound, has been found to possess antimicrobial, antioxidant, and anti-inflammatory activities, as well as the ability to inhibit the growth of cancer cells. These bioactive compounds work synergistically to provide the plant with its therapeutic benefits, supporting its traditional use in folk medicine to treat various health conditions.",
