    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Aquilaria parvifolia are resin tincture, decoction, infusion, tea, and essential oil. Resin tincture is prepared by mixing the resin of Aquilaria parvifolia with a solvent, typically ethanol, to create a concentrated liquid extract used for treating various health conditions. Decoction involves boiling the bark and roots of the plant in water to release its active compounds, which is then strained and consumed as a liquid extract. Infusion is a process of steeping the dried leaves and flowers of Aquilaria parvifolia in hot water to produce a flavorful and aromatic tea, while the leaves can also be made into a tea by steeping them in hot water. Essential oil is obtained through steam distillation of the resin of Aquilaria parvifolia, which is used in aromatherapy and as a natural remedy for various health issues.",
